n CO2 + NH3 if strict alignment with proton irradiation studies is desired\",\n        \"Clarify that CGP is a heterogeneous macromolecular reservoir rather than a single defined molecule\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.58,\n        \"rxn_008\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.95,\n        \"rxn_010\": 0.88\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.8,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.86,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.92,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.93,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.83,\n      \"feedback\": \"This hydrothermal-surface hybrid route is topologically useful and captures the intended environmental interconnection. Its weakness is the same as elsewhere: hydrothermal formaldehyde production from CO2 is not among the strongest literature-backed steps. Once formaldehyde is available, the downstream Strecker chemistry is solid.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_001\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Provide a stronger or alternative source of formaldehyde for surface Strecker chemistry\",\n        \"Consider atmospheric or photochemical formaldehyde production instead of hydrothermal-only sourcing\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.58,\n        \"rxn_005\": 0.96,\n        \"rxn_006\": 0.82,\n        \"rxn_007\": 0.76,\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.87,\n        \"rxn_012\": 0.89\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.8,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.87,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.95,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.9,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.84,\n      \"feedback\": \"This is a chemically interesting mixed-environment route with strong network connectivity and a credible terminal hydrothermal amination. It is weaker than P3 because it adds dependence on speculative hydrothermal formaldehyde generation while